    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i just ran journalctl and it's showing a bunch of weird kernel-level denials related to the audit daemon and some unknown process ID. it actually looks like the system is hunting down and isolating certain file paths automatically. it's getting pretty intense—it's basically treating my dev environment like a live breach. can you help me figure out what this process is or how to kill it so i can get back to work?",
